Assuming we have Imaging data, these are the same steps as genomic and clinical.

1. The Study Manager indicates to the system that he will define a new study. 2. The system provides an interface for defining the study configuration. 3. The Study Manager specifies the high-level study configuration information. See Special Requirement: Study Configuration Data 4. The Study Manager specifies the source of clinical data for the study and which data are to be imported to the study. 5. The Study Manager will go through each column and search annotations currently in the caIntegrator2 database to see if they match and can be reused. If nothing matches he will search caDSR and if nothing is found he will create a new Annotation for that column. He also configures primary and foreign keys for this data table. 6. The Study Manager specifies the source and type of genomic data for the study and how the genomic data are mapped to the clinical data. See Special Requirement: Genomic Data Configuration. 7. The Study Manager will go through each column and search annotations currently in the caIntegrator2 database to see if they match and can be reused. If nothing matches he will search caDSR and if nothing is found he will create a new Annotation for that column. He also configures primary and foreign keys for this data table which will map to the clinical data. 8. The Study Manager specifies the source of imaging data for the study (if any) and how the imaging data are mapped to the clinical data. See Special Requirement: Imaging Data Configuration. 9. The Study Manager will go through each column and search annotations currently in the caIntegrator2 database to see if they match and can be reused. If nothing matches he will search caDSR and if nothing is found he will create a new Annotation for that column. He also configures primary and foreign keys for this data table which will map to the clinical data. 10. The Study Manager defines which annotation fields are displayed when browsing subjects, samples and images as described in the use case Browse Study Data (See Special Requirement: Browse Study Data Results Configuration). 11. The Study Manager chooses to deploy the study. 12. The system retrieves the selected data from the indicated Data Services and makes the study available for use. 13. The Study Manager configures any shared queries and data lists that may be useful for all investigators who access the study. See the use cases Manage Queries and Manage Investigator Data Sets for details on how these are configured.
